result.formatted_address: Hong Kong, Causeway Bay, Kingston St, HK 香港島 Fashion Walk G2-3, 1/F, 9
result.name: Strokes Hong Kong

reviews.text:
A nice place to hang out to eat/play and spend a couple of hours. However the food and cocktails were so so, the food took quite a while. The bar and restaurant area gets pretty noisy when full.
The mini golf space was fun.

Fun day for the whole family plus granny as there are both quit and active games like ping pong, table football and indoor golf (9 holes or 14 holes). Costs HK$98 per person for unlimited play. Food and drinks on the pricey side but looked good. Next door craft brewery has some interesting beers. Good idea with children's parties and babies gatherings to spend the whole day (or just sneak off for some quick shopping).

Nice place, lot of people not even know its there, but do think its a restaurant bar that had some extra space and put a mini golf course in. And went with the cheapest they could get as its not high quality. And needs painting mor often to make fresh. High quality golf will sure bring in more customers as on a monday 5pm we was the only people there.

Strokes mini golf is now limited to 12 years and older.  Their food with cauliflower everything was also not satisfiable.  Garlic macaroni was nearly vomit inducing for the kids.  Just an over-priced hangout that you don’t think twice about.  Good luck!

Strokes was an amazing experience, surrounding us with beautiful decorations and neon lights it’s also a great idea to take photos there with friends. I brought my camera with me and took some great photos you wouldn’t think that you took in a mini golf area. The mini golf area has several ‘“levels’ and a score card, whoever gets the least hits to get the ball in the hole, wins. This was extremely fun not to mention funny with the courses in ‘Palm Springs’. Definitely would recommend and am looking forward to going another time.
